said radar operator <PERSON>Buck Benham</PERSON>, as he scanned the skies on his
radar scope in one of the four P3 trackers without the sophisticated
dome.
   Instead of chasing airborne suspects, <PERSON>Benham</PERSON> was trying to take
over the dome plane's detection job, which he likened to ``flying
around with a flashlight.''
