border. Only two countries provide timely assistance, according to
aircrews: the <LOCATION>Dominican Republic</LOCATION>, which will launch a military
aircraft on request, and the <LOCATION>Bahamas</LOCATION>, which places officers on
U.S.-flown helicopters.
   Crewmen said it is difficult to gain cooperation from <LOCATION>Mexico</LOCATION>.
Calls for assistance in chasing boats and planes have to be routed
through the federal government in <LOCATION>Washington</LOCATION>, and the process can
take four hours. In that time, smugglers often dump their loads or
land south of the border.
